  <name>GuitarHub</name>
  <summary>Aggregated guitar, amp, and pedal catalog browser</summary>

  <description>
    <p>
      GuitarHub is a native cross-platform desktop and mobile app that
      aggregates guitar, amp, pedal, and accessory listings from multiple
      online stores into a single unified catalog. Browse, search, and filter
      thousands of products — all offline, without ads, tracking, or
      registration.
    </p>
    <p>
      Key features:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Browse products from Reverb, MercadoLibre, and more</li>
      <li>Offline-first: full catalog synced to your device</li>
      <li>Fast full-text search with fuzzy matching</li>
      <li>Save items to your wishlist and track prices</li>
      <li>Community-extensible via source adapter plugins</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      GuitarHub is free and open source software (GPL-3.0). It never holds
      inventory, never processes payments, and never touches money — when you
      find a product you like, you are redirected to the original store to buy.
    </p>
    <p>
      Zero infrastructure cost: the scraper runs on GitHub Actions (free) and
      the catalog is served from GitHub Pages (free). No backend server ever.
    </p>
  </description>

